          <updateDate>2015-07-10T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of the House of Representatives that:</p> <ul> <li>Congress should establish a federal reapportionment system that would create compact and contiguous congressional districts that, to the greatest extent possible, follow geographic boundaries and county lines;</li> <li>congressional districts should not favor or disfavor an incumbent or political party;</li> <li>congressional districts should adhere to the existing standards of equal population; and</li> <li>the highest court of each state should have the power to reject congressional district maps that do not meet the above criteria.</li> </ul>]]></text>
